title: Major travel delays after lorry overturns in 'multi-vehicle' crash on M11
text:
Major travel delays after lorry overturns in 'multi-vehicle' crash on M11 Major travel delays after lorry overturns in 'multi-vehicle' crash on M11 MAJOR delays have struck road and rail after Storm Doris winds have caused chaos - including a multi-vehicle smash on the M11. PUBLISHED: 14:27,  41, Thu, Feb 23, 2017 Highways Agency The road is blocked by the pile-up which includes an overturned lorry 
One side of the motorway is currently completely blocked by the pile-up. 
A lorry lies on its side which cars appear to have been hit. 
The road is blocked northbound between J8 (Stansted A120) and J9 (A11). 
Queues are already building back to the turning for Stansted and Essex Poiice are on scene. 
Highways England tweeted to say they were dealing with a "serious" accident between junctions 9 and 10 - it is not clear if this is the same one. Related videos
